A significant number of CEOs are issuing strict Return-To-Office (RTO) mandates, arguing that remote work damages company culture and productivity. Many executives insist that returning full-time to the office is necessary for collaboration, brainstorming, and mentoring younger staff. As one industry leader stated during a recent town hall, "The data says teams are simply more productive in the office." Two-thirds of CEOs predict there will be a full return to the office by 2026, believing that forced hours spent in a traditional office create a necessary feeling of belonging and accountability that cannot be replicated over Zoom or Slack.
